article.headline: Providence 94, Maine 79
article.story: PROVIDENCE, R.I. (AP) -- Herbert Hill scored a career-high 27 points on 12-of-16 shooting and grabbed 11 rebounds to lead Providence past Maine 94-79 Saturday. Also scoring in double figures for Providence were Weyinmi Efejuku with 18, Sharaud Curry with 17 and Geoff McDermott with 16. The Friars (7-2), who have won six of their last seven games, now hold an 8-1 advantage over Maine all-time. Kevin Reed scored 21 for the Black Bears (4-5), who made a season-high 13 3-pointers, including 10 in the first half. Reed and Jon Sheets, who finished with 15 points, combined for eight 3-pointers in the first half. Maine shot out to a 6-0 lead on two 3's by Reed and surged ahead 35-26 on a three-point play by Phil Tchekane Bofia at 5:48 in the first half. Hill scored 15 in the first half to cut the deficit to 45-39 at halftime. Providence then made four steals and forced three turnovers during a 18-2 run in the first five minutes of the second half. Curry's layup with less than six minutes left gave the Friars their biggest lead at 86-67. After the intermission, Providence shot 59 percent, while holding Maine to 31 percent. Reed was held to two second-half points.
